Document: RDVertexAttribute
Path: godot/classes/class_rdvertexattribute.rst
Summary: Properties and methods for configuring vertex attribute data in a rendering device.

binding (int): The index of the buffer in the vertex buffer array to bind this vertex attribute. When set to -1, defaults to the attribute's index. Set via set_binding(value), get via get_binding(). Note: Cannot mix explicitly assigned bindings with implicitly assigned ones (-1). All attributes must use either explicit bindings or -1.

format (DataFormat): The way attribute data is interpreted when sent to a shader. Set via set_format(value), get via get_format().

frequency (VertexFrequency): The rate at which this attribute is pulled from its vertex buffer. Set via set_frequency(value), get via get_frequency().

location (int): The shader location this attribute is bound to. Set via set_location(value), get via get_location().

offset (int): Number of bytes between vertex buffer start and first instance of this attribute. Set via set_offset(value), get via get_offset().

stride (int): Number of bytes between consecutive instances of this attribute. Set via set_stride(value), get via get_stride().